## Scope

This slice owns the light-source layer: the net-new `SourceSpec` orchestration record wrapping the canonical `IncidentLightInfo`, the [Core] source editor that projects every editor field one-to-one onto `IncidentLightInfo` (with wavelength stored in canonical meters and converted only at the UI boundary), single-value-or-range wavelength/angle via the existing `RangedVariable`, and the [Standard] extensions — polarization presets and the Poincaré/ellipse picker, spectral source profiles, cone/acceptance averaging, coherent/incoherent/unpolarized flags, multiple simultaneous sources with weighted incoherent combination, and the Gaussian-beam angular-spectrum source. It treats `IncidentLightInfo` as the single canonical source value and MUST NOT fork it. The sweep machinery, photometric/CIE conversion, and project-file persistence are owned by Parts F/I and are out of scope. The only operator-UX trigger is Source-panel discoverability (E.10).

## Requirements

The following are the parent's Part E directives, reproduced verbatim. Contractful identifiers and `<file>:<line>` references are preserved exactly.

### R-1 (E.1) Source domain record (MUST, net-new, reuses `IncidentLightInfo`)

MUST add a new file `OpticalConstructor.Domain/SourceSpec.fs` to `OpticalConstructor.Domain.fsproj` (Part A assembly layout) defining the net-new orchestration record `SourceSpec` that wraps the canonical `IncidentLightInfo` (`Fields.fs:338`) and carries ONLY the orchestration fields that have no engine equivalent: a stable `sourceId`, an optional `name : string`, the per-source default unit of measure `displayUnit : UnitOfMeasure` (the `unitOfMeasure` `$def` owned by §A.7, projected to the `sourceSpec` `$def`), an optional `spectralProfile : SpectralProfile option` (E.4), an optional `cone : ConeAcceptance option` (E.5), an optional `gaussianBeam : GaussianBeamSpec option` (E.6), and `coherence : Coherence` (E.7). `SourceSpec` MUST store the base monochromatic state as one `IncidentLightInfo` value and MUST NOT duplicate its five fields. The record MUST be an immutable F# record (Part A constraint 1; CLAUDE.md). It MUST NOT carry any non-SI unit: wavelength lives inside `IncidentLightInfo.waveLength` whose `.value` is meters (`Fields.fs:284`), and `displayUnit` is a presentation-only tag.

### R-2 (E.2) [Core] Source editor → `IncidentLightInfo` projection (MUST)

MUST add `OpticalConstructor.Ui/Sources/SourceEditorView.fs` to `OpticalConstructor.Ui.fsproj` rendering the [Core] editor with one control per `IncidentLightInfo` field: wavelength (single value, with range deferred to E.3), incidence angle, polarization, ellipticity, and intensity. The view MUST be a pure FuncUI view function of the `SourceSpec` model and MUST emit messages that rebuild the underlying `IncidentLightInfo` via a single constructor function `SourceSpec.toIncidentLight : SourceSpec -> IncidentLightInfo`, which MUST be built on `IncidentLightInfo.create` (`Fields.fs:375`) for the normal-incidence case and `IncidentLightInfo.createInclined` (`Fields.fs:384`) for a non-zero angle, then set `polarization`/`ellipticity`/`refractionIndex` via record copy. The view MUST NOT call the 4×4 solver; producing fields is owned by Part F. Wavelength entry MUST accept the display unit chosen in `displayUnit` and convert to a `WaveLength` case (`Fields.fs:280`) at the boundary; nm and µm map directly to `WaveLength.Nm`/`WaveLength.Mkm` (`Fields.fs:294,295`), while Å, mm, eV, and cm⁻¹ MUST be converted to nm or µm via the §A.10 boundary conversions (Part D `Units.fs` `toWaveLength`, §D.2) before constructing `WaveLength` (the engine has no `WaveLength` case for those units — confirmed: only `Mkm | Nm` at `Fields.fs:280-282`). Intensity MUST be stored as a unit scalar `1.0` baseline on `SourceSpec`; the engine's relative R/T outputs (`FieldFunctions.fs` `intensity`, `:69`) are already normalized to incident, so intensity MUST act only as a per-source weight in multi-source averaging (E.8) and MUST NOT be threaded into `IncidentLightInfo`, which has no intensity field (`Fields.fs:338-345`).

### R-3 (E.3) [Core] Single-value-or-range wavelength and angle (MUST, reuses range primitives)

MUST express the "wavelength (single or range)" and angle inputs of the [Core] editor as a discriminated union `SourceAxis = Fixed of <value> | Ranged of RangedVariable` inside `SourceSpec.fs`, reusing `RangedVariable` (`Variables.fs:42`) for the ranged case rather than defining a new range type. For wavelength the ranged case MUST use `RangedVariable.WaveLengthRange` (`Variables.fs:46`) and for angle `RangedVariable.IncidenceAngleRange` (`Variables.fs:43`); preset spans MUST reuse the helpers in `StandardLightVariables.fs` (`wavelength200to800Range` `:64`, `incidenceAngleRange` `:40`, `polarizationRange` `:56`, `ellipticityRange` `:48`) instead of constructing fresh `Range<_>` values. The editor MUST surface a Fixed/Ranged toggle; when `Ranged` is chosen the produced `RangedVariable` MUST be handed to the sweep layer (Part F) unchanged. This part MUST NOT implement the sweep execution, charting, or `calculate`/`calculate3D` wiring (`Variables.fs`) — only the construction of the `RangedVariable` from operator input.

### R-4 (E.4) [Standard] Polarization presets + Poincaré/ellipse picker (MUST)

MUST add `OpticalConstructor.Ui/Sources/PolarizationPicker.fs` exposing the [Standard] presets s, p, 45°, RCP, LCP, and unpolarized as a preset list that sets `IncidentLightInfo.polarization`/`ellipticity` (and the `unpolarized` flag of E.7), reusing `Polarization.s` (`Fields.fs:322`), `Polarization.p` (`Fields.fs:323`), and `Polarization.create (Angle.degree 45.0)` (`Fields.fs:319`); RCP/LCP MUST set `Ellipticity.create 1.0`/`Ellipticity.create -1.0` (`Fields.fs:306`, which clamps to ±1). The picker MUST render the polarization ellipse and a Poincaré-sphere marker as a bidirectional control: dragging azimuth/ellipticity MUST write back `Polarization`/`Ellipticity`, and the live `StokesVector` readout MUST be computed from the produced incident `EmField` via `EmField.stokesVector` (`FieldFunctions.fs:44`) — the picker MUST NOT re-derive Stokes parameters by hand. `unpolarized` MUST be represented as the E.7 `Coherence.Unpolarized` flag, not as a sentinel `Polarization`/`Ellipticity` value. The 3D Poincaré rendering MUST reuse the OpenTK viewport stack named in Part A's `OpticalConstructor.Ui.fsproj` row; this part MUST NOT add a second 3D renderer.

### R-5 (E.5) [Standard] Spectral source profiles (MUST, net-new)

MUST define a net-new DU `SpectralProfile = Flat | Blackbody of double<K> | Illuminant of StandardIlluminant | LaserLine of WaveLength | ImportedSpectrum of string` in `SourceSpec.fs`, where `StandardIlluminant = D65 | A`, the `LaserLine` payload reuses `WaveLength` (`Fields.fs:280`), and `ImportedSpectrum` carries a sidecar path to a tabulated λ→weight spectrum. A `SpectralProfile` MUST be expanded — at the UI/IO boundary by a pure function `SpectralProfile.sample : SpectralProfile -> RangedVariable -> (WaveLength * float) list` in `SourceSpec.fs` — into a list of (wavelength, spectral weight) pairs over the wavelength range of E.3, each pair producing one `IncidentLightInfo` for the solver and a weight for E.8 averaging. The blackbody, D65, and A weight tables MUST be computed/stored in canonical SI (wavelength in meters via `WaveLength.value`, `Fields.fs:284`); temperature MUST be stored in kelvin. `ImportedSpectrum` MUST reference a sidecar by relative path under the JSON-canonical project (Part A constraint 4) and MUST be parsed with FSharp.Data (Part A storage seam); it MUST NOT be embedded as a `.binz` pickle of the project model. Photometric/CIE conversion of the resulting spectra is owned by the analysis part (Part F §F.8), not here.

### R-6 (E.6) [Standard] Cone / acceptance averaging (MUST, net-new)

MUST define a net-new record `ConeAcceptance = { halfAngle : Angle; samples : int }` in `SourceSpec.fs` (`Angle` is the engine geometry type already wrapped by `IncidenceAngle`, `Fields.fs:22`). A `ConeAcceptance` MUST be expanded by a pure function `ConeAcceptance.sample : ConeAcceptance -> IncidenceAngle -> IncidenceAngle list` that fans the base incidence angle into `samples` sub-angles across ±`halfAngle`, each producing one `IncidentLightInfo` via record copy on `incidenceAngle`. The expanded angles MUST be averaged on the OUTPUT side — over the solver's `StokesVector`/intensity results (`FieldFunctions.fs:44,69`) — and MUST NOT be averaged on the field amplitudes. Collimated illumination MUST be represented by the absence of a `ConeAcceptance` (`cone = None`), not by a zero-angle cone. Detector-acceptance averaging that belongs to a detector element is out of scope for this part; only the source-side cone is defined here.

### R-7 (E.7) [Standard] Coherent / incoherent and unpolarized flags (MUST, net-new)

MUST define a net-new DU `Coherence = Coherent | Incoherent | Unpolarized` in `SourceSpec.fs` carried on `SourceSpec.coherence`. `Coherent` is the default and MUST map directly to the engine's existing coherent solve (`OpticalSystemSolver`, `Solvers.fs:199`) with no change. `Incoherent` MUST be honored by routing the source through the engine's existing thick-substrate multi-reflection path — the substrate-driven `Multiple` solution branch (`Solvers.fs:152`, `Solution.create` at `:176`) that already sums intensities incoherently over internal reflections via `MultipleEmFieldSystem` (`Fields.fs:571`); this part MUST NOT add a separate incoherent solver. The per-layer coherent/incoherent split (thick substrate incoherent while films stay coherent) is a property of the stack/substrate (`Substrate = Plate | Wedge`, Part A §A.4 / `Media.fs:40`) owned by Part B — this directive owns ONLY the source-level flag that selects the path. `Unpolarized` MUST be expanded into the incoherent average of two orthogonal polarizations built from `Polarization.s`/`Polarization.p` (`Fields.fs:322,323`), averaged on `StokesVector`/intensity output (E.8), and MUST NOT be modeled by mutating `Ellipticity`.

### R-8 (E.8) [Standard] Multiple sources and averaging (MUST, net-new, reuses `MultipleEmFieldSystem`)

MUST allow a project to hold a list `sources : SourceSpec list` on the `OpticalConstructorProject` aggregate (the `sources` field declared in Part A §A.7); this part owns the `sourceSpec` `$def` shape and the list semantics. Each `SourceSpec` MUST expand — via a single pure function `SourceSpec.expand : SourceSpec -> (IncidentLightInfo * float) list` composing E.4/E.5/E.6/E.7 — into a list of weighted `IncidentLightInfo` values. The combined illumination MUST be evaluated by solving each expanded `IncidentLightInfo` with the existing single-system solver and combining the resulting `StokesVector`/intensity outputs as a weighted incoherent sum, reusing `StokesVector.(+)` and `StokesVector.Zero` (`Fields.fs:584,586`) for the accumulation; field-level (`EmField`) values MUST NOT be summed across sources. The weighted-sum reducer MUST live in `OpticalConstructor.Domain/SourceCombination.fs`. This part MUST NOT add caching of expanded source lists, retry logic, or a parallel scheduler; expansion is recomputed from the immutable `SourceSpec` on demand (Part A constraint 6).

### R-9 (E.9) [Standard] Gaussian-beam source (MUST, reuses FFT scaffolding)

MUST define a net-new record `GaussianBeamSpec = { waist : double<meter>; divergence : Angle }` in `SourceSpec.fs`, storing the beam waist in canonical meters (Part A constraint 3). The angular spectrum of the Gaussian beam MUST be generated by reusing the engine's existing scaffolding — `createGaussian` (`FourierTransform.fs:74`) for the Gaussian profile and the `FourierTransform` module (`FourierTransform.fs:137`) for the transform — inside a pure function `GaussianBeamSpec.angularSpectrum : GaussianBeamSpec -> WaveLength -> (IncidenceAngle * float) list` in `SourceSpec.fs`. This function MUST NOT introduce a new FFT, a new Gaussian generator, or a separate beam-propagation engine; it MUST produce a weighted set of plane-wave incidence angles that feed the same `expand`/averaging path as E.6/E.8. Beam propagation between curved elements (focusing) is owned by the curved-optics part (Part C), not here; this directive owns ONLY the source-side decomposition of the beam into weighted plane waves.

### R-10 (E.10) Operator UX — Source panel discoverability (MUST)

MUST register the Source editor (E.2) as a named entry in the constructor's element-palette/navigation so the operator can add a `Source` element (the `ConstructorElement.Source` case, Part A §A.4) and open its editor; the panel MUST be reachable from the palette without a hidden command. Because this part introduces no long-running background job and no destructive action, the remaining Operator-facing UX checklist items (progress granularity, pre-confirmation gate, completion→results refresh, opposing-action/undo, committable-file vs .gitignore) are NOT triggered here and MUST NOT be implemented in this part; sweep progress and results refresh are owned by Part F, and project-file persistence/undo by Part I. Adding a source MUST be a one-click palette action with no confirmation gate (a source is non-destructive and freely removable from the `sources` list of E.8).

## Non-requirements

- The `ConstructorElement.Source` case, the `BeamTree` head node, and the project `sources` field are owned by Part A (slice 001); this slice fills the `SourceSpec` record and expansion functions.
- The `UnitOfMeasure` DU and `toWaveLength`/conversion functions are owned by Part D (slice 002); the editor calls them at the boundary and MUST NOT re-implement conversions.
- Sweep execution, charting, `calculate`/`calculate3D` wiring, and photometric/CIE conversion are owned by Part F (slice 006).
- Project-file persistence, undo/redo, and recent files are owned by Part I (slice 009).
- Caching of expanded source lists, retry/error-wrapping shims, schema versioning, config knobs beyond the named per-source default unit, and migration code (§0 constraint 6).

